elyear=1993|certyear=1993|salesamount=1,000,000|refname=riaa}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Shaq}}\n\n[[Category:1993 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Shaquille O'Neal albums]]\n[[Category:Jive Records albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=April 2011}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Shaq Diesel\n| type       = album\n| artist     = [[Shaquille O'Neal]]\n| cover      = ShaqDiesel.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = October 26, 1993\n| recorded   = 1993<ref name=\"Diesel\">{{cite web|author=Keith Murphy|url=https://theundefeated.com/features/oral-history-shaq-shaquille-oneal-shaq-diesel-the-making-of-rap-hip-hop/|title='Shaq Diesel'|publisher=[[The Undefeated (website)|The Undefeated]]|date=2016-09-09|accessdate=2019-10-30}}</ref>\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 39:02\n| label      = {{flatlist|\n*[[Jive Records|Jive]]\n*[[RCA Records|RCA]]}}\n| producer   = [[Ali Shaheed Muhammad]], [[Def Jef]], [[Erick Sermon]], [[Main Source|K-Cut]], [[Meech Wells]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Shaq Fu: Da Return]]\n| next_year  = 1994\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Shaq Diesel\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[(I Know I Got) Skillz]]\n | single1date = September 7, 1993\n | single2     = [[I'm Outstanding]]\n | single2date = November 10, 1993\n | single3     = [[Shoot Pass Slam]]\n | single3date = January 4, 1994\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|2.5|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r188424}}</ref>\n| rev2      = [[Entertainment Weekly]]\n| rev2Score = mixed<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,308547,00.html |title=EW review |accessdate=2007-03-02 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070526100410/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,308547,00.html |archivedate=May 26, 2007 }}</ref>\n| noprose=yes\n}}\n'''''Shaq Diesel''''' is the debut album by professional basketball player and rapper, [[Shaquille O'Neal]], released on October 26, 1993 through [[Jive Records]].<ref name=\"Diesel\"/> The album features production from [[Ali Shaheed Muhammad]], [[Def Jef]], [[Erick Sermon]], [[Main Source|K-Cut]] and [[Meech Wells]], and guest appearances from Def Jef, [[Phife Dawg]] and [[Fu-Schnickens]].<ref name=\"Diesel\"/> \n\nDespite mixed to negative reviews, the album became a surprising success, reaching 25 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and eventually reaching platinum status on March 21, 1994 for shipping of one million copies.<ref>{{certification Cite|region=United States|title=Shaq Diesel|artist=Shaquille |type=album}}</ref>\n\nTwo singles from the album also managed to fare well on the charts, \"[[(I Know I Got) Skillz]]\", made it to #35 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and managed to reach gold status on December 21, 1993 for shipping of 500,000 copies, while \"[[I'm Outstanding]]\" made it to #47 on the Hot 100. A third single entitled \"Shoot Pass Slam\" was also released, but did not make it to the Billboard charts.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|extra_column = Producer(s)\n|title1 = Intro\n|note1 =\n|extra1 =\n|length1 = 1:48\n|title2 = [[(I Know I Got) Skillz]]\n|note2 = featuring [[Def Jef]]\n|writer2 = Shaquille O'Neal, Meech Wells, Jeffrey Fortson\n|extra2 = Def Jef, [[Meech Wells]]\n|length2 = 4:23\n|title3 = [[I'm Outstanding]]\n|note3 = \n|writer3 = O'Neal, Alisa Yarbrough, Erick Sermon, Raymound Calhoun\n|extra3 = [[Erick Sermon]]\n|length3 = 4:07\n|title4 = Where Ya At?\n|note4 = featuring [[Phife Dawg]]\n|writer4 = O'Neal, Ali Shaheed Muhammad, Malik Taylor\n|extra4 = [[Ali Shaheed Muhammad]]\n|length4 = 4:44\n|title5 = I Hate 2 Brag\n|note5 =\n|writer5 = O'Neal, Fortson, Wells, [[Herbie Hancock]]\n|extra5 = Def Jef, Meech Wells\n|length5 = 4:32\n|title6 = Let Me In, Let Me In\n|note6 =\n|writer6 = O'Neal\n|extra6 = Erick Sermon\n|length6 = 3:03\n|title7 = Shoot Pass 